The paper discusses improvements in the query complexity of traditional indexing algorithms based on minwise hashing, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) applications. The paper also discusses the use of 2-universal hashes, which are commonly used in data structures (DS) and information theory (IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS, cs.IR, and cs.DB, followed by cs.LG and cs.IT.
